<TITLE> PM urges quick climate aid for LDCs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 18 (bdnews24.com)  Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina urged rich countries to quickly disburse climate funds to help poor countries cope with changing weather. Pointing out that for poor countries diverting their funds to climate adaptation meant less for other more pressing development work, she said, "The funds needs to be disbursed immediately." Hasina made the call on Monday at a high level Asia-Pacific Dialogue on the Brussels Programmes of Action for the Least Developed Countries jointly organised by UN-ESCAP and the government, where she stressed on climate change in particular. Adaptation funds for climate change impact on least developed countries had been pledged at a UN climate summit last month in Copenhagen. The total package is expected to be about $10 billion per annum for three years till 2012 for poor countries and is set to increase thereafter. Hasina said transfer of much needed funds for coping with the adverse impacts of climate change was eroding Bangladesh's, as well as that of other poor countries, achievement in the UN Millennium Development Goals and other growth targets. She said the flow of funds to LDCs must be guaranteed considering Bangladesh's vulnerability to climate change and adverse impact of the financial crisis. Bangladesh was already affected by climate change, said Sheikh Hasina and elaborated that one metre rise of sea level, due to warmer temperatures, would inundate a fifth of Bangladesh displacing 20 million people. It would affect the livelihoods of 40 million by 2050, said H
